1.title: Prohibitive Costs
1.plot: At an estate auction in Huntingdon, Quebec, Valerie gets her hands on an old gangster hat that belonged to Meyer Lansky, while Mark leaves Billy crying over an expensive native baby carrier.

2.title: Formula for Success
2.plot: At a consignment auction in Montreal, Canada, Valerie tries to make the most of her hometown advantage. Mark outbids her on some sports memorabilia, and Billy hopes his gramophone will bring big returns back home.

3.title: Auction Prayers
3.plot: In Quebec City, Valerie, Mark and Billy go to an auction in a church, but it isn't a blessed affair for all of them. Billy overspends on circus masks, and Valerie buys a locked suitcase that contains President Taft's Kodak camera.

4.title: Titanic Deals!
4.plot: In Halifax, Valerie, Mark and Billy hope to find deep-sea treasure - but only Mark gets close to the water, getting his hands on a vintage battleship plaque and his feet into a pair of brass diver's slippers.

5.title: Burial Expenses
5.plot: Lodged in an industrial neighbourhood of Providence, Rhode Island, Christina's massive warehouse is home to more than 200 very strange items. We hope Billy, Valérie and Mark don't get too spooked because this is the auction of a lifetime.

6.title: Once a Pawn a Time
6.plot: In Tampa, Florida, Mark is looking for gators throughout the swamps. Billy is discovering he has more affiliation with communism than he might have thought while Valerie gets a peek on how secret societies' work.

7.title: Oils Well That Ends Well
7.plot: Buckaroo auctions is inundated with seized property and overflowing with inventory. They're having their biggest sale of the year which Billy, Valerie and Mark can't miss.

8.title: Live Free or Buy
8.plot: An antique and collectibles auction hosted by New Hampshire's one and only Auction Boss. Tired of dealing with Valerie and Mark, Billy brings a partner that will help him deal with both of them at the same time: his daughter Celina.

9.title: Blast from the Past
9.plot: For years, Laurence and Sally have shared their passion for buying collectibles with our Baggage Battles worldwide audience. Now, it's time for them to be on the other side of the auction block, where our buyers will either sink or swim.

10.title: Hometown Hero
10.plot: The Bohemia, Long Island consignment auction has a selection of pop culture items, vintage toys, medical equipment, sports memorabilia, and oddities. There's something for everyone.

11.title: Un-Beliebable Bargains
11.plot: Mark is the king when it comes to making money online, he has turned bulk buying into a science and is not about to miss a misguided freight auction. Billy and Valerie are not as familiar as Mark but they love hidden treasures. Will Mark teach them a trick or two about pallet poaching? Or will he send them on a wild goose chase?

12.title: Capital Gains
12.plot: Ottawa is Canada's capital city and politics is the name of the game here. Just like its neighbors to the south in Washington D.C., Ottawa is a city filled with scandals, cover-ups and secrets. Where there is big money, there is big business, and for Mark, Billy and Valerie: big deals.

13.title: Disco Deals
13.plot: The Big Apple is a city for dreamers and individuals with lots of ambition. Valerie is no exception and she's determined to show Mark and Billy that she'll stop at nothing to make a profit. The two New York wolves think Valerie is a mere lamb in the big city, and no real threat. They haven't seen anything yet.

9.title: Vancouver
9.plot: Comics and action figures go under the hammer at this police auction.

10.title: NYC Transit
10.plot: NYC Transit auction with over 14,000 items ready to auction. The loot includes mystery unknown parcels & a Stradivarius violin.

11.title: Toronto
11.plot: Toronto, Canada - lost or misplaced airport luggage is up for grabs, as well as rare postage stamps and photographic supplies.

12.title: North Carolina
12.plot: Greensboro N.C. where millions of pounds of lost or abandoned freight is up for auction.

1.title: Diamonds in the Rough
1.plot: The buyers are in Brooklyn, NY in search of international freight at the US Customs auction. Mark Meyer hopes to strike it rich bidding on solar panels, while the Martins face off against Billy Leroy to win a mystery sculpture.

2.title: Blast from the Past
2.plot: Mark Meyer, Billy Leroy, Laurence and Sally Martin are in Boston to turn a profit on American history. They battle for a 19th century musket, a hand-forged saw and historical documents - in hopes that these are authentic pieces.

3.title: Breaking the Bank
3.plot: The buyers are in Atlanta, GA, the freight capitol of the East Coast. Mark has his eyes set on a palette of aircraft parts, and the Martins decide whether or not to destroy an antique in order to reach unseen potential valuables.

4.title: Man on Fire
4.plot: The buyers travel to Greensboro, to compete for unclaimed southern treasure in this major hub. Mark has his eyes set on NASCAR fire suits, while Billy and the Martins battle over a vintage Arabic gun, inlaid with mother-of-pearl.

5.title: Cash Is King
5.plot: The buyers compete for lost and unclaimed bags from commercial airlines and private jets in St. Albans, England. Mark makes an interesting proposition to the previous owners of his newly acquired suitcase.

6.title: Knightwalkers
6.plot: Dublin, Ireland. Harry Houdini choice item takes the fancy of the Martins and a knight in shining armor might make an appearance.

7.title: Boy Toys
7.plot: NC Shipping Yard where lost freight includes a sewing machine and vintage toys. Featuring Mark, Billy and the Martins.

9.title: Grand Theft Auto
9.plot: The buyers bid on hundreds of lost or seized vehicles at the Tampa Machinery Auction. Everyone battles over a half-finished, vintage 1976 Corvette, and Mark discovers a rare gem left in the back seat of a vehicle up for auction.

10.title: California Scheming
10.plot: There is a hunt by the Martins for some classic movie posters and a shocking discovery is found by Billy.

11.title: Eye for an Eye
11.plot: Toronto - Freight and Baggage auction. There is a hunt by the Martins for some classic movie posters and a shocking discovery is found by Billy.

12.title: Liar Liar
12.plot: The buyers attend a well-kept secret - sheriff's auction in Shreveport, Louisiana. Billy scores a touchdown with his winnings, as a local sheriff interrogates Mark after buying his palette. Will there be a polygraph involved?

13.title: Daredevils
13.plot: The buyers travel north of the US border to bid on international freight and baggage. Billy & Laurence battle over vintage Samsonite luggage, and one of the experts finds an item manufactured by legendary daredevil, Evel Knievel.

14.title: Shock & Awe
14.plot: The buyers head to rural Louisiana to bid on Americana collected for over 50 years. Billy makes a "shocking" discovery among his winnings, and Mark misfires when he bids on the wrong item.

1.title: Guns A-Blazin'
1.plot: The buyers saddle-up to attend a Cowboy Auction in northern CA. Traci Lombardo makes a cameo, dueling with Sally over items from the Wild West, and one buyer finds a leather belt tied to legendary cowboy Buffalo Bill.

2.title: Mike Tyson's Punch Out
2.plot: Mark goes the distance at the Jacksonville estate auction for a giant Mike Tyson statue, and the Martins take extreme measures to open up one of their winnings. Billy hopes to make waves bidding on naval equipment.

3.title: Bunny Money
3.plot: The buyers head to Denver, hoping for a Rocky Mountain High profit. Billy and Mark scuffle over an authentic German World War II item, and one buyer gets excited after finding an original Playboy Bunny Costume.

4.title: Golden Ticket
4.plot: The buyers travel to Nashville, TN, where pop culture items are everywhere. Billy & Mark battle over a pink Cadillac front with an Elvis license plates, and one buyer scores a "Golden Ticket" after finding a Willy Wonka candy bar.

5.title: Blow Up
5.plot: The buyers attend an unclaimed crate auction in the Arizona desert, and things really heat up when one buyer tests a vintage bomb detonator using real explosives.

6.title: Platinum Hits
6.plot: In NYC, the buyers spar over memorabilia from some of the music's top icons. Billy and the Martins battle over a gold suit once worn by James Brown and one buyer tries to "Get Happy" with a Partridge Family lunchbox.

7.title: Sin City Win
7.plot: A Las Vegas Estate auction. A movie prop or replica goes under the hammer. Unlikely opponents team up to buy a vintage item.

8.title: World War Score
8.plot: The buyers march into battle at a once in a lifetime WWII D-Day auction in Normandy, France. They fight over rare relics, like battle-worn helmets and a gun holster used by Hitler's elite guard.

9.title: Two-Faced
9.plot: The buyers are in northern CA, home to a lucrative police auction. Billy bids on military trunks, Mark goes nutty over a stuffed squirrel, and one of the buyers discovers a mask mold of a famous Hollywood icon.

10.title: Bad Blood
10.plot: Buyers travel to Red Hook, NY, seeking wealth in pieces at a local estate sale. Billy banks on a WWII treasure and Mark hopes to fly high with a remote control helicopter while the Martins fight to hijack the profits.

11.title: What a Dummy
11.plot: The buyers visit a lucrative police auction in CA. Billy and Mark prove they aren't dummies as they bid on valuable mannequins, while the Martins gamble big on a vintage slot machine.

12.title: Lady Luck
12.plot: The auction action gets taken to a whole new level when Billy, Mark, and the Martins find themselves combatting new challenger, Traci Lombardo, in their quest for auction riches in Minnesota.

13.title: Space Case
13.plot: The buyers wage war in the west at a government-run auction in CA. Mark cuts into the Martins by bidding high on a box of knives, and Billy's profits skyrocket when he makes an astronomical find.

1.title: Steak Drum
1.plot: The buyers are back in Nashville, TN. The Martins bid big on an old Beatles drum after leading Mark to believe it's worthless, and one of the buyers scores a slam dunk with vintage Michael Jordan sneakers.

2.title: Monster Money
2.plot: The buyers are in Hollywood, CA, for one of the largest movie monster memorabilia auctions of all time. Billy bids on a replica C-3PO statue from Star Wars, and the buyers go "psycho" as they battle over an Alfred Hitchcock mask.

3.title: Intergalactic Bounty
3.plot: In Nashville, Tennessee, vintage and unusual items are the order of the day. A mysterious bag sends Mark off to the races while the contents of an old tube lead Billy to a beloved actor from the original Star Wars trilogy.

4.title: Big Boy Bucks
4.plot: The buyers are in Vegas, gambling on vintage casino and advertising items, like an iconic Bob's Big Boy Burger statue. A rare Elvis recording could mean a huge payday for one of the buyers, and Mark overpays for a slot machine.

5.title: Safari Sale
5.plot: The buyers travel to the other side of the world for a once-in-a-lifetime auction in South Africa. Billy traverses the outback to appraise a ceremonial mask from the Congo and a buyer wins an item worth $10,000 back in the US.

6.title: Inflated Egos
6.plot: The buyers are in Commerce, GA, seeking big returns. Billy finds himself enthralled with a coffin fashioned as an African bus, while the Martins and Traci challenge each other's expertise over a Ronald McDonald helium tank top.

7.title: Walk the Plank
7.plot: The buyers are in Orlando, FL, home to America's biggest theme parks. They do battle over Herbie the Love Bug, and one buyer believes a skeleton pirate up for bid is from Disney's Pirates of the Caribbean attraction.

8.title: Gunning for Dollars
8.plot: The buyers travel to Las Vegas for a gambling auction and win items that are both big and weird. Everyone sets their sights on a giant Gatling gun and the Martins discover a rare advertising piece from Nabisco Cookies.

9.title: Swami Says
9.plot: At an estate auction in Austin, TX, Billy hopes a Swami Fortune Telling Machine like the one in the movie Big holds good fortune for him, while the Martins and Mark dive into a bidding war for an underwater scooter.

10.title: It's Not Easy Making Green
10.plot: The buyers visit a retro collectibles auction in Allentown, PA. Mark bids high on a giant robot from a 1980s restaurant chain and one buyer discovers a Kermit the Frog puppet in a sealed case.

11.title: Dino-Mite
11.plot: In Knoxville, TN, the buyers do battle over vintage advertising. Sally breaks the bank bidding on an iconic dinosaur, and Billy's attempt at auction sabotage backfires.

12.title: Greedy Pig
12.plot: The buyers visit a "Man Cave" auction in Alpharetta, GA. Billy cons Mark into buying a replica Nazi dagger, and one of the buyers brings home the bacon after winning a giant inflatable pig.

13.title: The Wizard of Odd
13.plot: In Toronto, the buyers visit one of the world's largest lost property auctions. Mark is tuned-in to a giant old school boom box from the 80's, and one of the buyers finds a rare Wizard of Oz piece in a sealed trunk.

imdb.title: Baggage Battles
plot: Follows three teams of auction specialists who pick up unclaimed and lost personal property in a bid to turn a profit.::Anonymous
